and it's gonna happen to us.

309
00:16:34,676 --> 00:16:38,181
Well, okay, let's go.
Who's Tiny Tim?

310
00:16:39,724 --> 00:16:41,726
Hey, Moldy, do you
think Santa will be able to find...

311
00:16:41,726 --> 00:16:44,188
ElfCounty
under all this snow?

312
00:16:44,230 --> 00:16:48,985
I doubt it, Bubbles. We'll be
sad little elves this Christmas.

313
00:16:49,069 --> 00:16:50,987
- Oh, no!
- Oh, brother.

314
00:16:51,071 --> 00:16:53,073
- Where's your husband?
- Yeah. It's getting late.

315
00:16:53,156 --> 00:16:55,743
Said he went caroling
with Bart.

316
00:16:55,868 --> 00:16:59,747
We're in the money,
we're in the money

317
00:16:59,747 --> 00:17:03,085
We got a lot of
what it takes to get along

318
00:17:03,168 --> 00:17:05,254
I can't believe
I'm doing this.

319
00:17:05,379 --> 00:17:08,383
Can we open
our presents now, Dad?

320
00:17:08,424 --> 00:17:11,427
you know the tradition, son.
Not till the eighth race.

321
00:17:11,552 --> 00:17:13,764
Hey, Barney,
which one is Whirlwind?

322
00:17:13,889 --> 00:17:17,768
Number Six. That's our lucky dog
right over there.

323
00:17:17,893 --> 00:17:20,355
He's won
his last five races.

324
00:17:20,355 --> 00:17:22,857
What? That scrawny little
bag of bones?

325
00:17:22,983 --> 00:17:25,570
Come on, Dad. They're all
scrawny little bags of bones.

326
00:17:25,695 --> 00:17:28,072
Yeah, you're right.

327
00:17:28,197 --> 00:17:31,493
I guess Whirlwind is our only hope
for a Merry Christmas.

328
00:17:31,577 --> 00:17:33,870
Attention,
racing fans, we have a late scratch...

329
00:17:33,870 --> 00:17:35,872
in the fourth race.

330
00:17:35,872 --> 00:17:38,960
Number 8, Sir Galahad will be
replaced by Santa's Little Helper.

331
00:17:39,085 --> 00:17:43,089
Once again, Sir Galahad has been
replaced by Santa's Little Helper.

332
00:17:43,172 --> 00:17:45,175
Bart, did you hear that?

333
00:17:45,175 --> 00:17:47,177
What a name!
Santa's Little Helper!

334
00:17:47,261 --> 00:17:51,099
- It's a sign! It's an omen!
- It's a coincidence, Dad.

335
00:17:51,099 --> 00:17:54,185
- What are the odds on Santa's Little
Helper? - Ninety-nine to one.

336
00:17:54,269 --> 00:17:59,900
Wow! Ninety-nine times
thirteen equals... Merry Christmas!

337
00:17:59,984 --> 00:18:01,904
I got a bad feeling
about this.

338
00:18:01,987 --> 00:18:03,864
- Don't you believe in me, son?
- Uh--

339
00:18:04,031 --> 00:18:07,034
Come on, boy. Sometimes your faith
is all that keeps me going.

340
00:18:09,537 --> 00:18:12,040
Oh, go for it, Dad.

341
00:18:12,081 --> 00:18:15,878
That's my boy! Eveything on
Santa's Little Helper.

342
00:18:15,878 --> 00:18:18,297
Three cheers for Brainy!

343
00:18:18,297 --> 00:18:20,884
- Hip hip hooray!
- Yay!

344
00:18:20,967 --> 00:18:22,886
Unadulterated pap.

345
00:18:22,969 --> 00:18:25,472
It's almost 9:00.
Where's Homer anyway?

346
00:18:25,472 --> 00:18:28,476
It's so typical
of the big doof us to spoil it all.

347
00:18:28,476 --> 00:18:30,770
- What, Aunt Patty?
- Oh, nothing, dear.

348
00:18:30,895 --> 00:18:32,898
I'm just trashing
your father.

349
00:18:32,898 --> 00:18:34,900
Well, I wish you wouldn't...

350
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:39,280
because aside from the fact he has
the same frailties as all human belings.

351
00:18:39,405 --> 00:18:41,282
he's the only father I have.

352
00:18:41,407 --> 00:18:44,077
Therefore, he is
my model of manhood,

353
00:18:44,244 --> 00:18:48,582
